Russian Hog Herd May Rise, Cattle Inventory Shrink, USDA Says

-- B y   E l i z a b e t h   C a m p b e l l
-- 
2011-09-20T19:29:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-20/russian-hog-herd-may-rise-cattle-inventory-shrink-usda-says.html
Russia’s hog herd may climb to
49.665 million head in 2012, from an estimated 48.25 million
this year, the U.S. Department of Agriculture’s  Foreign
Agricultural Service  said in a  report  posted today on the
agency’s website.  Pork production may increase to 2.02 million metric tons,
up from an estimated 1.965 million this year, the agency said.  Russia’s cattle herd may shrink to 26.5 million head next
year, from an estimated 26.995 million in 2011, according to the
report. Beef production may drop to 1.385 million tons, from an
estimated 1.405 million tons.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elizabeth Campbell in Chicago at 
 ecampbell14@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steve Stroth at 
 sstroth@bloomberg.net . 